{
  "texts": [
    "Transfer learning was employed to predict specialized/general metabolism-related genes in Solanum lycopersicum (tomato) by leveraging well-annotated Arabidopsis genes (Moore et al., 2020).",
    "Another innovative approach, 'evolutionarily informed machine learning,' used an xgboost model trained on transcriptomic data in Arabidopsis to predict nitrogen-use efficiency (NUE) and related genes in maize (Cheng et al., 2021).",
    "With the advent of single-cell sequencing technology, challenges arise due to higher dimensionality and complexity (Bobrovskikh et al., 2021).",
    "Advanced algorithms like t-sne, umap, magic, phate, Saucie, and Beeline have been proposed to address these challenges and are prevalent in both human and plant studies (Van Dijk et al., 2018; Amodio et al., 2019; Becht et al., 2019; Pratapa et al., 2020; Wu and Zhang, 2020; Marand et al., 2021).",
    "The rapid advancements in biological data generation and ML development have opened up significant possibilities for unraveling complex biological information."
  ]
}